{"key":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01|Jer|3","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jer","chapter":3,"textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024","parserRevision":"v10","verses":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jer:3:1","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jer","bookOrder":23,"chapter":3,"verse":1,"text":"If a man divorces his wife","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jer:3:2","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jer","bookOrder":23,"chapter":3,"verse":2,"text":"Look to the barren heights and see.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jer:3:3","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jer","bookOrder":23,"chapter":3,"verse":3,"text":"This is why the showers haven’t come —","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jer:3:4","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jer","bookOrder":23,"chapter":3,"verse":4,"text":"Haven’t you recently called to me, “My Father!","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jer:3:5","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jer","bookOrder":23,"chapter":3,"verse":5,"text":"Will he bear a grudge forever?","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jer:3:6","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jer","bookOrder":23,"chapter":3,"verse":6,"text":"In the days of King Josiah the Lord asked me, “Have you seen what unfaithful Israel has done? She has ascended every high hill and gone under every green tree to prostitute herself there.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jer:3:7","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jer","bookOrder":23,"chapter":3,"verse":7,"text":"I thought, ‘After she has done all these things, she will return to me.’ But she didn’t return, and her treacherous sister Judah saw it.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jer:3:8","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jer","bookOrder":23,"chapter":3,"verse":8,"text":"I observed that it was because unfaithful Israel had committed adultery that I had sent her away and had given her a certificate of divorce. Nevertheless, her treacherous sister Judah was not afraid but also went and prostituted herself.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jer:3:9","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jer","bookOrder":23,"chapter":3,"verse":9,"text":"Indifferent to her prostitution, she defiled the land and committed adultery with stones and trees.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jer:3:10","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jer","bookOrder":23,"chapter":3,"verse":10,"text":"Yet in spite of all this, her treacherous sister Judah didn’t return to me with all her heart —only in pretense.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jer:3:11","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jer","bookOrder":23,"chapter":3,"verse":11,"text":"The Lord announced to me, “Unfaithful Israel has shown herself more righteous than treacherous Judah.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jer:3:12","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jer","bookOrder":23,"chapter":3,"verse":12,"text":"Go, proclaim these words to the north, and say,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jer:3:13","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jer","bookOrder":23,"chapter":3,"verse":13,"text":"Only acknowledge your guilt —","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jer:3:14","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jer","bookOrder":23,"chapter":3,"verse":14,"text":"“ ‘Return, you faithless children —this is the Lord’s declaration —for I am your master, and I will take you, one from a city and two from a family, and I will bring you to Zion.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jer:3:15","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jer","bookOrder":23,"chapter":3,"verse":15,"text":"I will give you shepherds who are loyal to me, and they will shepherd you with knowledge and skill.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jer:3:16","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jer","bookOrder":23,"chapter":3,"verse":16,"text":"When you multiply and increase in the land, in those days —this is the Lord’s declaration —no one will say again, “The ark of the Lord’s covenant.” It will never come to mind, and no one will remember or miss it. Another one will not be made.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jer:3:17","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jer","bookOrder":23,"chapter":3,"verse":17,"text":"At that time Jerusalem will be called The Lord’s Throne, and all the nations will be gathered to it, to the name of the Lord in Jerusalem. They will cease to follow the stubbornness of their evil hearts.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jer:3:18","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jer","bookOrder":23,"chapter":3,"verse":18,"text":"In those days the house of Judah will join with the house of Israel, and they will come together from the land of the north to the land I have given your ancestors to inherit.’”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jer:3:19","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jer","bookOrder":23,"chapter":3,"verse":19,"text":"I thought, “How I long to make you my sons","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jer:3:20","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jer","bookOrder":23,"chapter":3,"verse":20,"text":"However, as a woman may betray her lover,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jer:3:21","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jer","bookOrder":23,"chapter":3,"verse":21,"text":"A sound is heard on the barren heights:","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jer:3:22","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jer","bookOrder":23,"chapter":3,"verse":22,"text":"Return, you faithless children.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jer:3:23","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jer","bookOrder":23,"chapter":3,"verse":23,"text":"Surely, falsehood comes from the hills,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jer:3:24","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jer","bookOrder":23,"chapter":3,"verse":24,"text":"From the time of our youth","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jer:3:25","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jer","bookOrder":23,"chapter":3,"verse":25,"text":"Let us lie down in our shame;","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"}],"layout":{"bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jer","chapter":3,"paragraphStarts":[1,2,3,4,5,6,11,13,14,19,20,21,22,23,24,25],"headings":[{"beforeVerse":1,"text":"Wages of Apostasy"},{"beforeVerse":6,"text":"Unfaithful Israel, Treacherous Judah"},{"beforeVerse":19,"text":"True Repentance"}],"poetryBlocks":[{"beforeVerse":1,"level":1},{"beforeVerse":2,"level":1},{"beforeVerse":3,"level":1},{"beforeVerse":4,"level":1},{"beforeVerse":5,"level":1},{"beforeVerse":13,"level":1},{"beforeVerse":19,"level":1},{"beforeVerse":20,"level":1},{"beforeVerse":21,"level":1},{"beforeVerse":22,"level":1},{"beforeVerse":23,"level":1},{"beforeVerse":24,"level":1},{"beforeVerse":25,"level":1}],"studyByVerse":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jer:3:1","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"If "},{"kind":"footnote","marker":1,"text":"One Hb ms, LXX, Syr; other Hb mss read Saying: If"},{"kind":"text","text":" a man divorces his wife"}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[{"marker":1,"text":"One Hb ms, LXX, Syr; other Hb mss read Saying: If"}]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jer:3:2","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Look to the barren heights "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Dt 12:2","book":"Deu","ch